                        <interp inst="t18420919-name-796" type="given" value="ELIZA"></interp>ELIZA PARKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of William Parker. I was in my shop about a quarter after nine o'clock that night—I heard a cry of "Stop thief," and saw the prisoner running—I saw him throw something from him into the ditch, but I could not see what it was—I saw this looking-glass taken from the same part of the ditch.</p>
